在法国延。他于1188年与Matilda Marie Petite在爱尔兰庫迪 度布林度布林结婚。他们至少是3个儿子的父母。他去世于大约1215年在爱尔兰庫迪 米亞斯登善林吉勒享年60岁，埋葬在爱尔兰庫迪 米亞斯登善林吉勒。"},"hr":{"abt 1157–abt 1215":"oko 1157.–oko 1215.","1157–1215":"1157–1215","–Male":"preminuo","1157–Female":"1157–preminula","1189–1248":"1189–1248","1193–1218":"1193–1218","–1218":"–1218","1153":"1153.","1193":"1193","abt 1189":"oko 1189.","abt 1157":"oko 1157.","abt 1215":"oko 1215.","1248":"1248","1215":"1215","1157":"1157","1167":"1167","1189":"1189","1188":"1188.","Abt 1193":"1193.","1218":"1218","Killeen, Dunshaughlin, County Meath, Ireland":"Killeen, Dunshaughlin, County Meath, Irska","Dublin, County Dublin, Ireland":"Dublin, County Dublin, Irska","St Mary's, County Dublin, Ireland":"St Mary's, County Dublin, Irska","Guyenne, France":"Guyenne, Francuska","Dublin, Dublin, Ireland":"Dublin, County Dublin, Irska"},"cs":{"abt 1157–abt 1215":"okolo 1157–okolo 1215","1157–1215":"1157–1215","–Male":"Zesnulý","1157–Female":"1157–Zesnulá","1189–1248":"1189–1248","1193–1218":"1193–1218","–1218":"–1218","1153":"1153","1193":"1193","abt 1189":"okolo 1189","abt 1157":"okolo 1157","abt 1215":"okolo 1215","1248":"1248","1215":"1215","1157":"1157","1167":"1167","1189":"1189","1188":"1188","Abt 1193":"1193","1218":"1218","Killeen, Dunshaughlin, County Meath, Ireland":"Killeen, Dunshaughlin, County Meath, Irsko","Dublin, County Dublin, Ireland":"Dublin, County Dublin, Irsko","St Mary's, County Dublin, Ireland":"St Mary's, County Dublin, Irsko","Guyenne, France":"Guyenne, Francie","Dublin, Dublin, Ireland":"Dublin, County Dublin, Irsko"},"da":{"abt 1157–abt 1215":"omkring 1157–omkring 1215","1157–1215":"1157–1215","–Male":"Afdød","1157–Female":"1157–Afdød","1189–1248":"1189–1248","1193–1218":"1193–1218","–1218":"–1218","1153":"1153","1193":"1193","abt 1189":"omkring 1189","abt 1157":"omkring 1157","abt 1215":"omkring 1215","1248":"1248","1215":"1215","1157":"1157","1167":"1167","1189":"1189","1188":"1188","Abt 1193":"1193","1218":"1218","Killeen, Dunshaughlin, County Meath, Ireland":"Killeen, Dunshaughlin, County Meath, Irland","Dublin, County Dublin, Ireland":"Dublin, County Dublin, Irland","St Mary's, County Dublin, Ireland":"St Mary's, County Dublin, Irland","Guyenne, France":"Guyenne, Frankrig","Dublin, Dublin, Ireland":"Dublin, County Dublin, Irland"},"nl":{"abt 1157–abt 1215":"circa 1157–circa 1215","1157–1215":"1157–1215","–Male":"Overleden","1157–Female":"1157–Overleden","1189–1248":"1189–1248","1193–1218":"1193–1218","–1218":"–1218","1153":"1153","1193":"1193","abt 1189":"circa 1189","abt 1157":"circa 1157","abt 1215":"circa 1215","1248":"1248","1215":"1215","1157":"1157","1167":"1167","1189":"1189","1188":"1188","Abt 1193":"1193","1218":"1218","Killeen, Dunshaughlin, County Meath, Ireland":"Killeen, Dunshaughlin, County Meath, Ierland","Dublin, County Dublin, Ireland":"Dublin, County Dublin, Ierland","St Mary's, County Dublin, Ireland":"St Mary's, County Dublin, Ierland","Guyenne, France":"Guyenne, Frankrijk","Dublin, Dublin, Ireland":"Dublin, County Dublin, Ierland"},"en":{"abt 1157–abt 1215":"about 1157–about 1215","1157–1215":"1157–1215","–Male":"Deceased","1157–Female":"1157–Deceased","1189–1248":"1189–1248","1193–1218":"1193–1218","–1218":"–1218","1153":"1153","1193":"1193","abt 1189":"about 1189","abt 1157":"about 1157","abt 1215":"about 1215","1248":"1248","1215":"1215","1157":"1157","1167":"1167","1189":"1189","1188":"1188","Abt 1193":"1193","1218":"1218","Killeen, Dunshaughlin, County Meath, Ireland":"Killeen, Dunshaughlin, County Meath, Ireland","Dublin, County Dublin, Ireland":"Dublin, County Dublin, Ireland","St Mary's, County Dublin, Ireland":"St Mary's, County Dublin, Ireland","Guyenne, France":"Guyenne, France","Dublin, Dublin, Ireland":"Dublin, County Dublin, Ireland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Cusack","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Aileen, Brigid, Eamon, Fergus, Seamus.","Irish (of Norman origin): habitational name from Cussac in Guienne, France, named with the Gallo-Roman personal name <i>Cūcius</i> or <i>Cussius</i> + the locative suffix <i>-acum</i>. The surname died out in England, but is common in Ireland, where it was imported at the time of the Anglo-Norman invasion in the 12th century. It has been Gaelicized as <b>de Cíosóg</b>."],"variants":[{"name":"Cuzick","meanings":["Irish and English (Worcestershire): variant of   Cusack  . This form of the surname is no longer found in Ireland and is rare in Britain."]},{"name":"Cusick","meanings":["Irish and Scottish: variant of   Cusack  , now found predominantly in Scotland.","Americanized form of Polish   Kusik   or Czech <b>Kusík</b>, Slovak <b>Kúšik</b> and <b>Kušík</b>.","Americanized form of Croatian <b>Kusić</b>, Croatian and Serbian <b>Kušić</b> (see   Kusic  ), or Serbian <b>Ćušić</b> (see   Cusic  )."]}]},{"name":"Geoffrey","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Of Germanic (Frankish and Lombard) origin, introduced to Britain by the Normans. It was in regular use among the counts of Anjou, ancestors of the English royal house of Plantagenet, who were descended from Geoffrey Plantagenet, Count of Anjou (  1113–51 ). It was a particularly popular name in England and France in the later Middle Ages; notable bearers in England include the poet  Geoffrey Chaucer  (  <i>c.</i>1340–1400 ) and in Wales the chronicler  Geoffrey  of Monmouth (  d. 1155 ). The original form and meaning of the name is disputed. According to one theory, it is merely a variant of   Godfrey ;  others derive the first part from the Germanic word <i>gawia</i> ‘territory’, <i>walah</i> ‘stranger’, or <i>gisil</i> ‘pledge’. Medieval forms can be found to support all these theories, and it is possible that several names have fallen together, or that the name was subjected to reanalysis by folk etymology at an early date."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Mo'r","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Traditional name from <i>mór</i> ‘large, great’. This was the commonest of all girls’ names in late medieval Ireland, and has continued in use in both Ireland and Scotland to the present day."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1355923,"age":10,"year":"1167","julianDay":2147298,"description":"Arrival of Normans at Baginbun in Co. Wexford thus started 800 year struggle between English and Irish.","jurisdictionLevel":3}],"lifeSummary":"Geoffrey Mo'r Cusack was born about 1157, in Guyenne, France as the son of Mr Cusack. He married Matilda Marie Petite in 1188, in Dublin, County Dublin, Ireland. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. He died about 1215, in Killeen, Dunshaughlin, County Meath, Ireland, at the age of 60, and was buried in Killeen, Dunshaughlin, County Meath, Ireland."},"et":{"abt 1157–abt 1215":"umbes 1157–umbes 1215","1157–1215":"1157–1215","–Male":"Surnud","1157–Female":"1157–Surnud","1189–1248":"1189–1248","1193–1218":"1193–1218","–1218":"–1218","1153":"1153","1193":"1193","abt 1189":"umbes 1189","abt 1157":"umbes 1157","abt 1215":"umbes 1215","1248":"1248","1215":"1215","1157":"1157","1167":"1167","1189":"1189","1188":"1188","Abt 1193":"1193","1218":"1218","Killeen, Dunshaughlin, County Meath, Ireland":"Killeen, Dunshaughlin, County Meath, Iirimaa","Dublin, County Dublin, Ireland":"Dublin, County Dublin, Iirimaa","St Mary's, County Dublin, Ireland":"St Mary's, County Dublin, Iirimaa","Guyenne, France":"Guyenne, Prantsusmaa","Dublin, Dublin, Ireland":"Dublin, County Dublin, Iirimaa"},"fi":{"abt 1157–abt 1215":"noin 1157–noin 1215","1157–1215":"1157–1215","–Male":"Kuollut","1157–Female":"1157–Kuollut","1189–1248":"1189–1248","1193–1218":"1193–1218","–1218":"–1218","1153":"1153","1193":"1193","abt 1189":"noin 1189","abt 1157":"noin 1157","abt 1215":"noin 1215","1248":"1248","1215":"1215","1157":"1157","1167":"1167","118